# Rift Exchange Frontend Project

## Current Development Focus
We are implementing enhancements to the Rift Exchange frontend with a focus on UI polish, wallet integration, and compliance features.

## Key Features Being Implemented

### 1. Asset Selector Styling
- Match the asset selector UI exactly to the Jumper interface design
- Consider pulling components directly from Jumper's open source repository if compatible
- Ensure consistent styling, animations, and behavior with the reference implementation
- Pay special attention to hover states, selection indicators, and asset icons/logos

### 2. Wallet Integration
- Replace the current Rainbow/WalletConnect implementation with Reown AppKit integration
- Follow Reown documentation at https://reown.com/appkit for proper implementation
- Ensure wallet connection state properly persists across sessions where appropriate
- Implement proper error handling for connection failures

### 3. Compliance Implementation
- Add Chainalysis/TRM OFAC compliance screening to all transactions
- Implement geoblocking for sanctioned regions:
  - North Korea
  - Iran
  - Other US-sanctioned regions
- Add address screening to block blacklisted ETH addresses on wallet connection
- Implement BTC address validation to block sanctioned addresses when pasted
- All compliance checks should provide appropriate user feedback without exposing screening details

## Code Structure and Standards

### Components
- Use TypeScript for all new components
- Follow existing project naming conventions
- Create reusable components for compliance messaging

### State Management
- Use Zustand for state management throughout the application
- Improve the current Zustand implementation where possible
- Ensure proper loading, error, and success states are handled in store
- Keep store logic separated by domain (wallet state, transaction state, etc.)

### Styling
- Use project's existing CSS/styling approach (CSS modules, styled-components, etc.)
- Maintain responsive design across all screen sizes
- Ensure accessibility standards are maintained

## Dependencies and APIs
- Reown AppKit for wallet integration
- Chainalysis/TRM APIs for compliance checking
- Geolocation service for regional restrictions

